<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 04 at 1:35AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southwestern Chouteau
and northeastern Cascade Counties through 215 AM MDT...
At 134 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 16 miles west of Fort Benton to 9 miles
northwest of Belt. Movement was northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Fort Benton, Highwood, Carter, Shonkin, Floweree and Tracy.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
